# Auditor Station configuration.
# Copy this file to ".env" (same folder) and edit. ".env" is gitignored — your PIN never
# commits and never rides in the shared bundle. Set the PIN on the auditor's laptop.
#
#   cp .env.example .env      (then edit STATION_PIN)
#
# Restart the station (pnpm start) after changing anything here.

# Access PIN. Ask the auditor what they want, put it here.
# Leave BLANK or remove the line = station is OPEN (no PIN). To change it: edit and restart.
# To remove it: clear the value (or delete .env) and restart.
STATION_PIN=

# At-rest encryption passphrase (SQ2-7). If set, build with the SAME key:
#   STATION_DB_KEY=... ; pnpm build:catalog   → produces data/catalog.db.enc (no plain db)
# The laptop needs this same key in its .env to open the catalog. Leave blank = plain dev DB.
# Keep this key OUT of the shared bundle — deliver it separately from the catalog.
STATION_DB_KEY=

# --- Optional overrides (sensible defaults apply if omitted) ---
# STATION_PORT=8717
# STATION_MODEL=qwen2.5:7b        # qwen2.5:3b is ~2x faster on CPU (lighter narration, same numbers)
# STATION_OLLAMA_URL=http://localhost:11434
# STATION_NUM_PREDICT=512         # cap tokens per answer; lower = faster/shorter (e.g. 300)
#
# SPEED on slow CPUs — the deterministic tools already produce cited, non-punitive answers,
# so the LLM narration is optional:
# STATION_NARRATE=false           # skip the 2nd model call; answer = tool summary (much faster)
# STATION_DETERMINISTIC=true      # skip the LLM entirely; router picks the tool (near-instant)
